							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lesliejamison/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Screen-Shot-2019-09-25-at-11.49.34-AM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" alt="Leslie Jamison" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lesliejamison/">Leslie Jamison</a></h6>
										Leslie Jamison is the New York Times bestselling author of <em>The Recovering, The Empathy Exams, Make it Scream, Make it Burn</em>, and a novel, <em>The Gin Closet</em>. She is a contributing writer at The New York Times Magazine, and her work has appeared in numerous other publications including <em>The Atlantic, The Paris Review</em>, and <em>Harper’s</em>. She teaches at Columbia University and lives in Brooklyn with her daughter.																			</div>
